details.description: Immerse yourself in the vibrant atmosphere of The Bowl at Ballantyne, a captivating destination where culinary delights, enriching experiences, and natural beauty converge. Stroll along the picturesque stream park, savor delectable flavors at a diverse array of eateries, and indulge in pampering services that elevate your every day. Discover a world of endless possibilities at The Bowl, where every moment is crafted to inspire and delight.

reviews_data.review_text: Worked and lived in the area for almost 8-years right next to the Ballantyne Hotel. It's incredible how much the Ballantyne Bowl changed the culture of the area by mixing a wonderful green space/park with tons of Charlotte's up and coming food and drink spots. Wonderful place for the family or just grab a bite to eat and sit outside a bit and enjoy the atmosphere.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your review, Justin! We hope to see you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Very good! Service and the food.

With everything they tore down to build all of this they could have better parking options. It took us 30 minutes to find parking. We went to Bossy Beulah's for dinner, Do not recommend. Food was bland and expensive, not worth the cost. The woman at the table next to us couldn't even eat her sandwich. Beulah can keep that recipe a secret.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Carrie, thanks for your feedback! The Bowl was built to be more pedestrian-friendly with most parking options located on the outskirts of the property. For all parking options, please visit https://thebowlnc.com/pages/parking. As for your experience at Bossy Beulah's, we are sorry to hear this. We recommend reaching out to that business about your experience.

reviews_data.review_text: Had a great time at a show here and some good restaurants around too.

reviews_data.review_text: This place is amazing. There was a lot of restaurants nice and beautiful park. Nice hang out spot. (Hang out) 10/10.     (The park) 8/10. Feed back for the park a little more activity.  But still amazing.(Hotels) 9/10 I know I have not been in all but some were a little clumped. But if I had to rate the Balentine hotel that will be a 10/10. Over all thought’s, this place is amazing best time to come is around 10:00pm to 12:00 am. There’s a nice fountain to sit buy the park is so modern. And there’s a mini rock climbing. A nice walk area and if you are a hotel guest then you can go in there nice spa, pool and the nice 1900 hundred type bar. So over all score. 20/10. Definitely recommend. And yes I will definitely return, have a good night and nice work.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Sheetal, thank you for your review and feedback! We're glad you had a great time at The Bowl.

reviews_data.review_text: Worked and lived in the area for almost 8-years right next to the Ballantyne Hotel. It's incredible how much the Ballantyne Bowl changed the culture of the area by mixing a wonderful green space/park with tons of Charlotte's up and coming food and drink spots. Wonderful place for the family or just grab a bite to eat and sit outside a bit and enjoy the atmosphere.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your review, Justin! We hope to see you again soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Very good! Service and the food.

With everything they tore down to build all of this they could have better parking options. It took us 30 minutes to find parking. We went to Bossy Beulah's for dinner, Do not recommend. Food was bland and expensive, not worth the cost. The woman at the table next to us couldn't even eat her sandwich. Beulah can keep that recipe a secret.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Carrie, thanks for your feedback! The Bowl was built to be more pedestrian-friendly with most parking options located on the outskirts of the property. For all parking options, please visit https://thebowlnc.com/pages/parking. As for your experience at Bossy Beulah's, we are sorry to hear this. We recommend reaching out to that business about your experience.

reviews_data.review_text: This place is amazing. There was a lot of restaurants nice and beautiful park. Nice hang out spot. (Hang out) 10/10.     (The park) 8/10. Feed back for the park a little more activity.  But still amazing.(Hotels) 9/10 I know I have not been in all but some were a little clumped. But if I had to rate the Balentine hotel that will be a 10/10. Over all thought’s, this place is amazing best time to come is around 10:00pm to 12:00 am. There’s a nice fountain to sit buy the park is so modern. And there’s a mini rock climbing. A nice walk area and if you are a hotel guest then you can go in there nice spa, pool and the nice 1900 hundred type bar. So over all score. 20/10. Definitely recommend. And yes I will definitely return, have a good night and nice work.
